of the groups management board as from  september  for an initial term of three years until  august  the five months transition period will ensure a smooth handover of responsibilities as well as a continuation in the management of the company frank posnanski  will continue in his role as cfo and member of the management board under the leadership of ronny verhelst the tele columbus group evolved from a regional infrastructure company into a digital multimedia provider and a strong number three in the german cable market over the last couple of years the financial restructuring of tele columbus and the successful ipo were followed by the integration of the cable companies number four and five in the german market and hence the consolidation of all mediumsized cable players in germany with the upcoming introduction of a new and consolidated brand in autumn  i will have accomplished my mission at tele columbus to make the company fit for the future states the native belgian ronny verhelst i would like to thank all my colleagues at tele columbus for their fantastic commitment as well as all our partners for the excellent cooperation over the past seven years at the same time i would like to ask for their understanding regarding my decision to relocate my focal point of life to my home in belgium it is almost impossible to adequately value ronnys achievements with his vast experience his strategic skillset his strong execution capability and his drive he successfully managed to turn the company around comments frank donck chairman of the supervisory board of tele columbus ag in the name of the entire supervisory board i would like to thank ronny for his achievements and we wish him all the best for his professional and private future at the same time we are very happy to have won with timm degenhardt a highqualified and experienced successor with a strong commercial background and customer focus timm is also truly familiar with the telecommunications and infrastructure market and over the past couple of years actively shaped the digitalisation of the media industry in several key positions together with him we would like to continue the growth path for tele columbus german timm degenhardt is joining from the swiss telecommunications provider sunrise most recently as chief consumer officer and member of the management board with responsibility for the entire consumer business prior to this he was chief marketing officer and chief commercial officer at sunrise since  and with his drive for both customer orientation and digitalisation laid foundations for the successful sunrise ipo previously timm degenhardt was ceo at aizo group a smart home applications company since  and senior vice president marketing  sales at eon ag since  this was preceded by several senior leadership positions at american express and at the telecommunications provider orange where he was a member of the management board and vice president for marketing and product development since  timm degenhardt holds a master of science in marketing management from nottingham business school and a degree level diploma in marketing from the chartered institute of marketing in london i am very excited to commence my new role because i am truly convinced that the new digital applications the growing demand for media content and the increasing mobile usage will offer great opportunities for a high performance broadband internet and entertainment provider such as tele columbus states timm degenhardt who will join the companys management effectively  august  the german market has to catch up a lot in international comparisons when it comes to innovation and adaption of new tech and media trends in my opinion a nationwide yet also locallyfooted provider like tele columbus offers excellent opportunities to tap that potential about tele columbus the sdax listed tele columbus group is one of germanys largest cable network operators via its origins  individual regional cable network operators that were merged into tele columbus  the company dates back to  today about  million connected households in germany are served by tele columbus primacom pepcom deutsche telekabel martens und kms with tv signals and increasingly digital broadcast packages internet and voice connections provided via highperformance broadband cable as a national provider with a regional focus and a partner of the housing industry the group is present throughout its core markets berlin brandenburg saxony saxonyanhalt and thuringia as well as in numerous key regions in western germany in tune with current demand trends the company is upgrading its networks in a hybrid fibreoptic infrastructure for superfast internet connections of up to several hundred megabits per second with the stateoftheart internet transmission standard docsis  the broadband cable caters to the entire range of innovative media applications from analogous digital and highdefinition tv to highspeed internet and voice connections to telemetry services tenant portals and interactive services beyond merely transmitting signals tele columbus uses its own product platform in order to actively increase the programme offering and to develop additional services via its company hl komm tele columbus also delivers powerful connections and network services to business customers contacthannes lindhuberdirector communications phone     fax      pressetelecolumbusde wwwtelecolumbuscom  dissemination of a corporate news transmitted by dgap  a service of eqs group agthe issuer is solely responsible for the content of this announcementthe dgap distribution services include regulatory announcements financialcorporate news and press releases archive at wwwdgapde language englishcompany tele columbus ag kaiserinaugustaallee   berlin germanyphone    fax     email hanneslindhubertelecolumbusdeinternet wwwtelecolumbusdeisin detcagwkn tcagindices sdaxlisted regulated market in frankfurt prime standard regulated unofficial market 